<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97F39FDB4FD1A84B8" author="Mendes" box="[368,686,639,664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa, 2063, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">Mendes &amp; Andersen (2009)</bibRefCitation>
for the adult; 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97D18FDB4FBE684B8" author="Pinder" box="[849,1106,639,664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Pinder, L. C. V. &amp; Reiss, F. (1986) 10. The pupae of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region - Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region. Keys and diagnoses. Part 2. Pupae. Entomologica scandinavica, 28 (Supplement), 299 - 456." type="journal article" year="1986">Pinder &amp; Reiss (1986)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97A29FDB4FADF84B8" author="Adam" box="[1120,1387,639,664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97EDEFD6FFE7B849C" author="Mendes" box="[151,463,676,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa, 2063, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">Mendes &amp; Andersen (2009)</bibRefCitation>
for the pupa; and 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97CD0FD6FFC21849C" author="Pinder" box="[665,917,676,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Pinder, L. C. V. &amp; Reiss, F. (1983) 10. The larvae of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region - Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region. Keys and diagnoses. Part 1. Larvae. Entomologica scandinavica, 19 (Supplement), 293 - 435." type="journal article" year="1983">Pinder &amp; Reiss (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97DE8FD6FFB1E849C" author="Adam" box="[929,1194,676,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97AFCFD6FFF5584C0" author="Mendes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa, 2063, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">Mendes &amp; Andersen (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97F50FD0CFE5384C0" box="[281,487,711,736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Epler, J. H., Ekrem, T. &amp; Cranston, P. S. (2013) 10. The larvae of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic Region - Keys and diagnoses. In: Andersen, T., Cranston, P. S. &amp; Epler, J. H. (Sci. Eds.), The larvae of Chironomidae (Diptera) of the Holarctic Region. Keys and diagnoses. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, 66 (Supplement), 387 - 556." type="journal article">
Epler 
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97F15FD02FE3984C0" box="[348,397,711,736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
for the larva. No amendment is required to accommodate the new species described here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40614D095525FFC97E8EFCC4FE6C85FC" blockId="1.[151,1436,604,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
Generally the male of the genus differs from those of other 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97D2CFCC4FC408508" box="[869,1012,783,808]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Chironomini">Chironomini</taxonomicName>
genera in the foretibia bearing a long spur on the apical scale, one to several dorsal projections on the anal tergite (abdominal tergite IX), and the poorly developed transverse sternapodeme in the hypopygium. The males of some Neotropical species have no dorsal projection on the anal tergite, but these can be recognized by the following features: foretibia bearing a long spur on the conical apical scale, and transverse sternapodeme usually absent or when present without oral projections (
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97ED7FC0FFE7885FC" author="Mendes" box="[158,460,964,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Mendes, H. F. &amp; Andersen, T. (2009) Neotropical Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921, with the description of thirteen new species (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa, 2063, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">Mendes &amp; Andersen 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40614D095525FFC97E8EFC2CFE49824C" blockId="1.[151,1436,604,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
The pupa is similar to that of 
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97C5CFC2CFD168220" box="[533,674,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Polypedilum</emphasis>
, but recognizable by the abdominal setation. 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97AEDFC2CFA9C8220" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1921" box="[1188,1320,999,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97AEDFC2CFA9C8220" box="[1188,1320,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Nilothauma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a pair of LS-seta on abdominal segment IV and a long, taeniate, dorsal seta on the anal lobe. In 
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97AFCFBC7FAF68205" box="[1205,1346,1036,1061]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Polypedilum</emphasis>
, all the lateral setae on abdominal segment IV are simple and the dorsal seta on the anal lobe is simple or absent (
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97B7CFBE4FEA2824D" author="Pinder" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Pinder, L. C. V. &amp; Reiss, F. (1986) 10. The pupae of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region - Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region. Keys and diagnoses. Part 2. Pupae. Entomologica scandinavica, 28 (Supplement), 299 - 456." type="journal article" year="1986">Pinder &amp; Reiss 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97F69FB9FFE45824C" author="Saether" box="[288,497,1108,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Saether, O. A., Andersen, T., Pinho, L. C. &amp; Mendes, H. F. (2010) The problems with Polypedilum Kieffer (Diptera: Chironomidae), with the description of Probolum subgen. n. Zootaxa, 2497, 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="2010">
Saether 
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97F3CFB9EFE12824D" box="[373,422,1108,1133]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40614D095525FFC97E8EFBBCFE7282F8" blockId="1.[151,1436,604,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
The larva resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97FB4FBBCFD2682B0" box="[509,658,1143,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Paratendipes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97FB4FBBCFD2682B0" box="[509,658,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Paratendipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the mentum has small median teeth, but differs as the antennae are lacking Lauterborn organs (
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97F95FB57FD538294" author="Adam" box="[476,743,1180,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97DD6FB57FB808295" box="[927,1076,1180,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Paratendipes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97DD6FB57FB808295" box="[927,1076,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Paratendipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has Lauterborn organs on the antennal segments 2 and 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40614D095525FFC97E8EFB2FFA3F8300" blockId="1.[151,1436,604,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
<bibRefCitation id="244F30F85525FFC97E8EFB2FFE7882DC" author="Adam" box="[199,460,1252,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether (1999)</bibRefCitation>
divided the genus 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97CD4FB2FFC9582DD" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1921" box="[669,801,1252,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97CD4FB2FFC9582DD" box="[669,801,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Nilothauma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into four species groups, the 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97A21FB2FFB6682DD" authorityName="Adam &amp; Saether" authorityYear="1999" box="[1128,1234,1252,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duminola">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97A21FB2FFB6682DD" box="[1128,1234,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">duminola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97A96FB2FFA9182DD" baseAuthorityName="Rempel" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[1247,1317,1252,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="babiyi">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97A96FB2FFA9182DD" box="[1247,1317,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">babiyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97B7BFB2FFAD982DD" baseAuthorityName="Goetghebuer" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[1330,1389,1252,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brayi">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97B7BFB2FFAD982DD" box="[1330,1389,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">brayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="87DE368A5525FFC97EDEFAC2FEB88300" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1927" box="[151,268,1289,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictipenne">
<emphasis id="72AA911B5525FFC97EDEFAC2FEB88300" box="[151,268,1289,1312]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">pictipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups, on the basis of the adult morphology. However, most of the immature forms remain unknown.
</paragraph>
